Bernard Gitau @benagitau The government has warned artistes and musicians against contravening the Films and Stage Plays Act or face arrest and prosecution. Kenya Film and Classifications Board (KFCB) chief executive Ezekiel Mutua issued the warning after controversial photos of artiste Esther Akoth popularly known as Akothee emerged online. “They have resulted to daring the government by stretching the bounds of freedom by promoting immorality and defiling our common decency,” said Mutua. He said the board has received many complaints from the public on the trend of sexualising content and stage performances in public places.